summary:
5. Confirms the necessity of additional troops and police for Côte d’Ivoire’s stabilization; 

6. Reiterates the Special Representative of the Secretary-General’s role in certifying the upcoming legislative elections; 

7. Decides UNOCI’s mandate: 

   a. Protection and security: 
      - Protect civilians from imminent physical violence; 
      - Develop a comprehensive strategy for civilian protection; 
      - Work with humanitarian agencies; 
      - Monitor and report on violations against vulnerable populations; 

   b. Address remaining security threats and border-related challenges: 
      - Support national authorities; 
      - Monitor and deter militias and armed groups; 
      - Address cross-border security challenges; 
      - Liaise with the FRCI; 
      - Support security for Government members and key stakeholders; 

   c. Monitoring of the arms embargo: 
      - Monitor implementation of measures; 
      - Inspect and collect arms brought into Côte d’Ivoire in violation of the embargo.
The Security Council resolution 2000 (2011) outlines the following key tasks:

(d) Collection of weapons:
- Assist national authorities in collecting, registering, securing, and disposing of weapons and clearing explosive remnants of war.
- Support community weapons collection programs linked to violence reduction and reconciliation.
- Ensure collected weapons are not disseminated or re-utilized outside a comprehensive national security strategy.

(e) Disarmament, demobilization, and reintegration programme (DDR):
- Assist in developing and implementing a new national DDR program with clear individual criteria.
- Support registration and screening of former combatants.
- Support disarmament and repatriation of foreign armed elements.

(f) Reconstitution and reform of security and rule of law institutions:
- Assist in conducting a sector-wide review of security institutions and developing a comprehensive national security strategy.
- Support effective coordination, transparency, and harmonization of efforts in security sector reform (SSR).
- Advise on security sector reform, provide training, and support capacity development.
